; update-ingest.fk — one recipe by which ANY channel ingests an update; trust is RE-DERIVABILITY.
;
; The runnable heart of update-ingest-as-recipe.form (GAP-U0 closed). Every channel — mesh neighbor,
; file pull, llm summary, sensor stream, git delta — ingests through ONE recipe; what differs is a single
; field: nativeness, and nativeness is whether we can RE-DERIVE the offer over data we observed.
;
; Modeled minimally and exactly: an offer carries a re-derivable recipe (a b) and an observed input x,
; the value the channel CLAIMS, and whether the channel is native. The delta's value is re-derived as
; (a*x + b) — our own walk. Trust = the re-derivation reproduces the claim (no trust in the channel).
; Champion-challenger: a re-derived delta takes the slot only by OUT-DERIVING the incumbent champion;
; else it melts back. A non-native (opaque) offer is never adopted — we cannot walk it, so it stays
; quarantined as hypothesis even when its claimed value would improve. Summarization falls out: a summary
; is an update on a channel; a native summary is rederivable, a non-native one is oracle-not-master.
;
; Composes (by reference; each already four-way): slice-update-roundtrip.fk (delta-as-cell transport),
; champion-challenger.fk (the out-derive gate). Pure-compute ops only -> crosses four-way (fkwu).
; Proven by: form-stdlib/tests/update-ingest-band.fk (verdict 63, four-way at validate.sh).

(do
    ; re-derive the delta's value from its recipe (a b) over observed input x — our own walk
    (defn ui-derive (a b x) (add (mul a x) b))

    ; trust = re-derivability: 1 iff our walk reproduces the channel's claim (no trust in the channel)
    (defn ui-rederives? (a b x claimed) (eq (ui-derive a b x) claimed))

    ; champion-challenger: the challenger out-derives the incumbent champion (higher is better)
    (defn ui-beats? (champ a b x) (gt (ui-derive a b x) champ))

    ; adopt iff NATIVE and RE-DERIVED and it OUT-DERIVES the champion — three gates, in that order
    (defn ui-adopt? (champ native a b x claimed)
        (if (eq native 1)
            (if (eq (ui-rederives? a b x claimed) 1)
                (ui-beats? champ a b x)
                0)
            0))

    ; THE ONE RECIPE every channel ingests through: adopt the re-derived value, else keep the champion
    ; (melt-back on a weaker native delta; quarantine on a non-native one — the same keep, one recipe)
    (defn ui-ingest (champ native a b x claimed)
        (if (eq (ui-adopt? champ native a b x claimed) 1)
            (ui-derive a b x)
            champ))

    0)
